WEBVTT

00:04.166 --> 00:04.533
- Croatia is the Med's

00:04.533 --> 00:04.734
- Croatia is the Med's
hidden gem.

00:06.166 --> 00:07.300
- Three, two, one!

00:07.300 --> 00:08.667
- It's a beautiful coast.

00:08.667 --> 00:10.500
It has, like, hundreds
of islands.

00:10.500 --> 00:12.533
- Everything about this place
is just gorgeous.

00:12.533 --> 00:14.300
- I mean, how can you not
like Croatia?

00:14.300 --> 00:16.000
They filmed "Game of Thrones"
here.

00:16.000 --> 00:17.700
- I put you in
the naughty corner.

00:17.700 --> 00:18.700
I'm actually back
to do this again.

00:18.700 --> 00:20.667
Surprise, bitches.

00:20.667 --> 00:22.700
This year, I'm gonna try
a bit of a softer approach,

00:22.700 --> 00:25.100
'cause apparently I can be
a little bit scary sometimes.

00:25.100 --> 00:27.166
Don't tell me to take a walk
from my own pantry,

00:27.166 --> 00:28.533
'cause that's just annoying.

00:28.533 --> 00:30.400
But sweet don't pay
the paychecks.

00:30.400 --> 00:32.166
- Last charter season,
I was super green.

00:32.166 --> 00:33.300
I still am green.

00:33.300 --> 00:35.000
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
- Whoa.

00:35.000 --> 00:37.033
- I asked you to put it
on the track--you said track.

00:37.033 --> 00:38.567
- Go home, Bobby.

00:38.567 --> 00:40.433
- When it comes to looking
for a perfect woman...

00:40.433 --> 00:42.567
If we weren't here, if it was
a different situation,

00:42.567 --> 00:44.033
you'd be interested.

00:44.033 --> 00:45.700
- Um...
- I will find mine.

00:45.700 --> 00:47.300
- When I'm on charter,
it is go time.

00:47.300 --> 00:49.166
Don't even look at me wrong.

00:49.166 --> 00:50.266
I'm gonna wear whatever
the f--- I want to wear,

00:50.266 --> 00:51.333
'cause this is my galley.

00:51.333 --> 00:53.033
I always go after what I want.

00:53.033 --> 00:55.166
- Are you single?

00:55.166 --> 00:57.333
I'm a chef.
I can't help myself.

00:57.333 --> 00:59.734
- Think of me as
one of the deck boys.

00:59.734 --> 01:01.066
I grew up with
five older brothers

01:01.066 --> 01:02.734
who are super adventurous.

01:02.734 --> 01:05.200
And I think I can take most
things that they throw at me.

01:05.200 --> 01:06.667
- And I whooped your ass!

01:06.667 --> 01:10.700
- 26, and I'm not looking
to be "wifed up."

01:10.700 --> 01:12.533
- That's how you cause problems,
hesitating like that.

01:12.533 --> 01:14.133
Being a bosun,
you got to please the captain.

01:14.133 --> 01:15.533
You got to please the guests.

01:15.533 --> 01:18.667
- Oh, my goodness!
It's amazing.

01:18.667 --> 01:21.066
- I don't want to fail,
and that's my biggest fear,

01:21.066 --> 01:23.467
other than snakes, is failing.
[chuckles]

01:23.467 --> 01:25.066
- What about when
they're in a hot tub?

01:26.734 --> 01:28.500
- No, no, no.
- I'm just one of them guys

01:28.500 --> 01:30.200
that someone ask me
to do something, I'm like,

01:30.200 --> 01:31.767
"Yeah, yeah, I'll do that."

01:31.767 --> 01:33.100
And then I'll get there,
and I'm like,

01:33.100 --> 01:34.367
"Oh, how do I do this thing?"

01:34.367 --> 01:36.333
- Am I tucking you in?

01:36.333 --> 01:38.100
I'm a very positive person.

01:38.100 --> 01:39.333
Tomorrow's a new day.

01:39.333 --> 01:40.734
- Always a new day.

01:40.734 --> 01:42.767
- Seriously, somehow people
always drag me

01:42.767 --> 01:44.467
into their issues.

01:44.467 --> 01:46.100
You've been a bad boy,
haven't you, Wes?

01:46.100 --> 01:47.333
- I've been very conflicted.

01:47.333 --> 01:49.333
- Dr. Bugsy's job is done.

01:49.333 --> 01:52.033
- I said a-boom,
Team Sirocco.

01:52.033 --> 01:54.200
Team Sirocco,
chick-a-boom.

01:54.200 --> 01:56.333
When I tell people I was
an NFL cheerleader,

01:56.333 --> 01:58.767
they, like, assume that
I'm, like, some floozy.

01:58.767 --> 02:00.600
But I'm not.

02:00.600 --> 02:03.633
- People have a hard time
thinking that a female

02:03.633 --> 02:05.266
could actually drive a boat,

02:05.266 --> 02:07.133
which I find funny.

02:07.133 --> 02:09.066
Always keep your eyes on me.

02:09.066 --> 02:10.400
You have to use
your common sense.

02:10.400 --> 02:12.266
I know you're used
to running the boat.

02:12.266 --> 02:13.667
That's not gonna happen here.

02:13.667 --> 02:16.200
Professionalism is everything.

02:16.200 --> 02:17.533
- Stop, stop!
Sh--.

02:17.533 --> 02:19.333
- That can never happen.
- Stop! Stop! Sh--.

02:19.333 --> 02:20.633
- I'm not here to make friends.

02:20.633 --> 02:21.633
I'm here to work.

02:21.633 --> 02:23.533
- I f---ing dare you!

02:23.533 --> 02:25.400
Being at sea makes
everyone nuts.

02:25.400 --> 02:28.200
- Goddamn!
There's just so much blood!

02:28.200 --> 02:29.667
- F--- you, bro.
- No, no, no, no!

02:29.667 --> 02:31.400
- Anyone?
Anyone?

02:31.400 --> 02:33.400
- I should just leave.
I feel like such a weak link.

02:33.400 --> 02:36.100
- You can't become a leader
by being a dick.

02:36.100 --> 02:37.133
[boat horn honks]

02:37.133 --> 02:40.133
[upbeat music]

02:40.133 --> 02:47.166
♪ ♪

02:52.166 --> 02:55.166
[lively salsa music]

02:55.166 --> 03:01.300
♪ ♪

03:01.300 --> 03:03.233
- The only time I've been
to Croatia

03:03.233 --> 03:04.633
was for a music festival,

03:04.633 --> 03:06.233
and from what I can remember,

03:06.233 --> 03:08.000
I think it was a great time.

03:09.633 --> 03:11.700
How are you going?
- Good, welcome aboard.

03:11.700 --> 03:13.533
- Good, thank you.
- How was your trip?

03:13.533 --> 03:15.400
- Good.
I came from France.

03:15.400 --> 03:17.000
I'm Hannah.
- Sandy.

03:17.000 --> 03:18.433
both:
Nice to meet you.

03:18.433 --> 03:20.700
- I've been a yacht captain
for 27 years.

03:20.700 --> 03:22.700
Boated from Bahamas,
New England,

03:22.700 --> 03:24.400
Western Med, Eastern Med,

03:24.400 --> 03:26.066
Red Sea, Persian Gulf.

03:26.066 --> 03:27.700
Chartering has a lot of rules.

03:27.700 --> 03:30.467
Being a charter captain,
I have a lot of rules.

03:30.467 --> 03:32.600
It's really important
that the chief stew and I

03:32.600 --> 03:36.567
have a good relationship,
because I ask a lot of you.

03:36.567 --> 03:38.700
And I'm not a micromanager,
but I do observe.

03:38.700 --> 03:40.567
- Yeah.
- And in this industry,

03:40.567 --> 03:42.166
I have an image.
- Yeah.

03:42.166 --> 03:43.333
- And I don't want
to ruin the image.

03:43.333 --> 03:45.200
- No, that's perfect.

03:45.200 --> 03:47.533
My one and only time that
I've had a female captain,

03:47.533 --> 03:49.033
it really didn't go very well.

03:49.033 --> 03:51.400
She was basically just
a micro-manager

03:51.400 --> 03:53.400
with no self-awareness.

03:53.400 --> 03:54.734
And if she's like that,

03:54.734 --> 03:56.533
it probably
won't end well this time.

03:56.533 --> 03:58.467
- Here we have
your two stewardesses.

03:58.467 --> 03:59.667
- Ah.

03:59.667 --> 04:02.033
This one looks familiar--
Lauren.

04:02.033 --> 04:04.600
- I'm gonna let you go ahead
and sort out the uniforms.

04:04.600 --> 04:06.467
This boat needs to be
turned around,

04:06.467 --> 04:07.700
and we don't have
a lot of time.

04:07.700 --> 04:09.333
So we're gonna do
a walk-through.

04:09.333 --> 04:10.767
- Okay, excellent.
- Okay, awesome.

04:10.767 --> 04:13.066
- [sighs heavily]

04:13.066 --> 04:16.100
[driving techno music]

04:16.100 --> 04:17.567
♪ ♪

04:17.567 --> 04:19.333
- Every cabinet I open...

04:19.333 --> 04:21.233
[plate clatters]

04:21.233 --> 04:22.467
Needs organized.

04:22.467 --> 04:23.633
- By the sounds of it, yeah.

04:23.633 --> 04:25.500
On many super-yachts,

04:25.500 --> 04:28.500
what you see on the outside
is absolute perfection.

04:28.500 --> 04:30.633
Then when you start
diving a little deeper,

04:30.633 --> 04:32.700
you realize it really
needs organization.

04:32.700 --> 04:34.567
- Hello.
- Hi.

04:34.567 --> 04:36.500
- My name's Adam.
- Adam, Sandy.

04:36.500 --> 04:37.734
- Pleasure to meet you, Sandy.
- Welcome aboard.

04:37.734 --> 04:39.100
- Hi, Hannah.
- Hi, nice to meet you.

04:39.100 --> 04:40.633
- Nice to meet you.
- Oh, wow.

04:40.633 --> 04:42.333
- Happy to be here.
Let's do some cookin'.

04:42.333 --> 04:44.100
When I'm on charter,
I'm busting my ass.

04:44.100 --> 04:45.333
But when I finish,
I live in a van.

04:45.333 --> 04:46.700
It's the land yacht.

04:46.700 --> 04:48.633
Hit highway one.
I go for a surf.

04:48.633 --> 04:50.266
I chill out.
The plan's no plan.

04:50.266 --> 04:51.633
What?
- Not a porthole.

04:51.633 --> 04:52.734
- I got a window?

04:52.734 --> 04:54.133
- Adam is like Jake Gyllenhaal

04:54.133 --> 04:55.767
and Daniel Craig mixed together.

04:55.767 --> 04:57.400
He's very easy on the eyes.

04:57.400 --> 04:59.333
[funky music]

04:59.333 --> 05:01.100
- Come on up.

05:01.100 --> 05:03.000
- Stock it up.
I could get used to this.

05:03.000 --> 05:04.100
Hey, there.
How you doing?

05:04.100 --> 05:05.600
- Hi.
- Wesley.

05:05.600 --> 05:07.266
- Hannah, nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

05:07.266 --> 05:09.367
- I'm the boson.
- Boson, okay, perfect.

05:09.367 --> 05:11.367
You'll be sharing with the--
the chef.

05:11.367 --> 05:12.600
It's really close
to the galley.

05:12.600 --> 05:14.000
- Don't worry about that.
- Yeah?

05:14.000 --> 05:15.133
- Yeah, I'm a pretty
good sleeper.

05:15.133 --> 05:16.467
- We'll get you some earplugs.

05:16.467 --> 05:18.066
- I'll be all right.
Don't panic.

05:18.066 --> 05:19.400
- So what's going on?

05:19.400 --> 05:21.233
- I know your job's
really demanding.

05:21.233 --> 05:24.500
So when you have time to rest,
I want you to rest.

05:24.500 --> 05:26.000
- I intend to.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.233
- Come to me with
any of your issues.

05:28.233 --> 05:30.100
- Are you the first mate?

05:30.100 --> 05:32.166
- No, I'm the captain.

05:32.166 --> 05:35.166
- Okay.
[claps hands]

05:35.166 --> 05:37.000
I thought you were
the chief stew.

05:37.000 --> 05:38.300
- Female captains are rare,

05:38.300 --> 05:40.033
so this happens often.

05:40.033 --> 05:41.433
And I'm not offended.

05:41.433 --> 05:42.767
If the food sucks...
- Yeah.

05:42.767 --> 05:44.400
- The charter sucks.
- Game over, yeah.

05:44.400 --> 05:46.633
- No pressure.
I don't want to keep you.

05:46.633 --> 05:49.033
- Perfect, I apologize
for misunderstanding

05:49.033 --> 05:50.033
your position on the boat.

05:50.033 --> 05:51.400
F---.

05:51.400 --> 05:52.633
Pleasure to meet you, Captain.
- You, too.

05:52.633 --> 05:53.633
- See you soon.
- Okay.

05:53.633 --> 05:57.667
♪ ♪

05:57.667 --> 05:59.033
- Not that way.
Hello?

05:59.033 --> 06:00.033
- Hi.

06:00.033 --> 06:02.567
- Hi, nice to see you.

06:02.567 --> 06:05.266
- Is it automatic,
or do I push it?

06:05.266 --> 06:07.033
I got to get inside.

06:07.033 --> 06:08.300
Oh, there.

06:08.300 --> 06:10.033
- How you doing?
Roomies, man.

06:10.033 --> 06:11.100
- What's up, buddy?
Get on in here.

06:11.100 --> 06:12.467
- Name's Wesley.

06:12.467 --> 06:14.066
- Getting along already.
I love it.

06:14.066 --> 06:16.000
- I've got some cheat sheets
and stuff,

06:16.000 --> 06:18.033
but I'm just gonna wait till,
uh, the other stewardess comes.

06:18.033 --> 06:19.567
And I saw your CDL.
I was like,

06:19.567 --> 06:21.467
"I know your face is familiar
from somewhere."

06:21.467 --> 06:23.200
I think I met you in
New York, didn't I?

06:23.200 --> 06:24.567
- Yes.
- When I was there with Bobby.

06:24.567 --> 06:26.200
- Hello.
- Welcome aboard.

06:26.200 --> 06:27.533
- Thank you so much.
I'm happy to be aboard.

06:27.533 --> 06:29.266
- Well, we have a lot
of work to do.

06:29.266 --> 06:31.734
- Last charter season,
I made some really good tips.

06:31.734 --> 06:33.266
I quit the fire department

06:33.266 --> 06:35.000
and I got some braces

06:35.000 --> 06:37.433
to get some new teeth.

06:37.433 --> 06:39.700
- When I have everyone here,
I'll have a crew meeting.

06:39.700 --> 06:40.700
- Sounds good.

06:40.700 --> 06:42.300
Schnitzel.

06:42.300 --> 06:44.567
I can't even say anything
with S's.

06:44.567 --> 06:46.600
How are you?
- Nice to see you.

06:46.600 --> 06:48.000
- Yeah, I know.
This is a nice boat.

06:48.000 --> 06:49.200
- It's nice, hey?
- Hi.

06:49.200 --> 06:50.333
- What's up?
- How are you?

06:50.333 --> 06:52.066
- [giggles]
Nice to see you.

06:52.066 --> 06:53.500
- I met Lauren at a nightclub
with Bobby.

06:53.500 --> 06:55.367
She was one of his
three dates.

06:55.367 --> 06:57.433
So I've got my fingers crossed

06:57.433 --> 07:00.100
that she's better at her job
than she is at choosing men.

07:00.100 --> 07:01.600
Come up and I'll
give you your uniform.

07:01.600 --> 07:02.633
- Okay.

07:02.633 --> 07:06.633
[upbeat electronic music]

07:06.633 --> 07:08.333
- Is this your room?

07:08.333 --> 07:09.500
- It's kind of lesser
of two evils, though,

07:09.500 --> 07:11.166
'cause they're both tiny.

07:11.166 --> 07:12.367
- I think the bottom
looks bigger in that room.

07:12.367 --> 07:13.700
- All right.

07:13.700 --> 07:15.333
- Lauren and I met in New York,

07:15.333 --> 07:17.500
and we hooked up
and had a short little fling

07:17.500 --> 07:19.100
for, you know, a month or two,

07:19.100 --> 07:20.767
and, um, I recommended
her for the job.

07:20.767 --> 07:24.166
That ended, and now
we're working together.

07:24.166 --> 07:26.600
So I hope things aren't
gonna be awkward.

07:26.600 --> 07:28.233
Are guys getting V-necks,
do you know?

07:28.233 --> 07:29.500
Or do I have a chick shirt?

07:29.500 --> 07:31.066
- Sorry.
I don't know.

07:31.066 --> 07:32.600
- Ugh.

07:32.600 --> 07:34.200
- I expect a lot,

07:34.200 --> 07:36.066
so when I ask you
to do something,

07:36.066 --> 07:37.400
it's important to me
that it gets done.

07:37.400 --> 07:38.633
- Yeah.
My dad always raised me

07:38.633 --> 07:40.233
to work hard
and follow the rules.

07:40.233 --> 07:42.100
However, one time
I did push the boundaries

07:42.100 --> 07:44.333
and got caught drinking
with my rugby friends

07:44.333 --> 07:46.500
and got suspended from school.

07:46.500 --> 07:48.633
[music wanes]

07:48.633 --> 07:51.066
- When we're on charter,

07:51.066 --> 07:53.467
this door is always open.
- Okay.

07:53.467 --> 07:55.633
- So what happens in here
must look...

07:55.633 --> 07:57.533
- It's a guest area, sure.
- Absolutely.

07:57.533 --> 07:59.266
So you have a big job
ahead of you.

07:59.266 --> 08:00.633
- Hi.
- Hi.

08:00.633 --> 08:02.100
- Watch out, the bulge is open.
I'm Lauren.

08:02.100 --> 08:03.467
- I'm Bugs.
Nice to meet you.

08:03.467 --> 08:05.000
- Nice to meet you.
Can you say your name again?

08:05.000 --> 08:06.367
- Bugs, like Bugs Bunny.
You know, bunny.

08:06.367 --> 08:08.066
Just Bugs.
- Oh, my God, I love that.

08:08.066 --> 08:10.000
It's nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, too.

08:10.000 --> 08:11.467
My real name's
actually Christine.

08:11.467 --> 08:13.734
But my parents used to call me
"little bug."

08:13.734 --> 08:15.367
And, uh, it kind of just stuck.

08:15.367 --> 08:17.033
- Where are you from?
- I'm from South Africa.

08:17.033 --> 08:18.400
- Cool.

08:18.400 --> 08:20.433
- I just finished up being
a chief stew

08:20.433 --> 08:23.000
on a private-owned
charter yacht for about a year.

08:23.000 --> 08:25.533
I decided to take a sabbatical,
do some travels.

08:25.533 --> 08:27.433
And now, seeing as though
it's the end of the season,

08:27.433 --> 08:30.266
decided this is the perfect
time to make a quick buck

08:30.266 --> 08:32.433
before I get back
in the chief game.

08:32.433 --> 08:34.166
You need help with anything?

08:34.166 --> 08:37.100
- It's in French.
I can't read this.

08:37.100 --> 08:38.533
- I think we can
move everything out

08:38.533 --> 08:40.100
and then work our way
putting it all back in

08:40.100 --> 08:41.567
in an even area.
- Okay.

08:41.567 --> 08:45.433
[lively dance music]

08:45.433 --> 08:46.667
- So that's it?

08:46.667 --> 08:48.567
- How you doing?

08:48.567 --> 08:50.700
- Bobby.
- Hey, there. Wes.

08:50.700 --> 08:52.633
- Nice to meet you, Max.
Yeah, cool, cool.

08:52.633 --> 08:54.500
I've got some things that we
need you to start up with

08:54.500 --> 08:56.133
at forward.

08:56.133 --> 08:58.500
How long you been
working on boats for?

08:58.500 --> 08:59.600
- No, that's all right.

08:59.600 --> 09:01.166
- I worked on two boats,

09:01.166 --> 09:03.066
that haven't actually
left the dock.

09:03.066 --> 09:04.433
But, you know, it's yachting.

09:04.433 --> 09:05.467
How hard can it be, you know?

09:05.467 --> 09:07.266
I can sit and watch the Eskimos.

09:07.266 --> 09:08.467
Towel?
- So there you go.

09:08.467 --> 09:09.600
- Have some fun.

09:09.600 --> 09:11.066
- Well, who's this?

09:11.066 --> 09:12.400
What's your name?

09:12.400 --> 09:14.200
- Malia.
- Hi, Malia.

09:14.200 --> 09:15.600
- Are you...?
- Nice to meet you.

09:15.600 --> 09:17.133
My name's Adam.
I'm the chef.

09:17.133 --> 09:18.600
- Nice to meet you.
- Yeah.

09:18.600 --> 09:20.734
- I meet a lot of deckhands
over the last ten years,

09:20.734 --> 09:22.333
and, um...

09:22.333 --> 09:24.700
needless to say,
none of them look like Malia.

09:24.700 --> 09:26.066
[laughs]

09:26.066 --> 09:27.600
- Hmm.

09:27.600 --> 09:29.400
[upbeat music]

09:29.400 --> 09:30.600
- Hey, guys.
- Hey, how you doing?

09:30.600 --> 09:32.133
- Hi.
- Hi.

09:32.133 --> 09:33.166
- Malia.
- I'm Bobby, nice to meet you.

09:33.166 --> 09:34.200
- Nice to meet you.

09:34.200 --> 09:36.467
- My God, Malia is a total babe.

09:36.467 --> 09:37.600
I'm in trouble.

09:37.600 --> 09:38.600
So where you from?
- Hawaii.

09:38.600 --> 09:40.200
- That's rad.

09:40.200 --> 09:41.367
- Been teaching scuba diving
out there.

09:41.367 --> 09:42.633
So I've worked on boats,

09:42.633 --> 09:44.333
but I haven't worked
on a nice boat.

09:44.333 --> 09:47.100
Just sh-- dive boats, so...
- Okay, no worries.

09:47.100 --> 09:48.500
We all start somewhere.

09:48.500 --> 09:52.500
♪ ♪

09:52.500 --> 09:54.500
- Bugs.
- Oh, how's it--Wes.

09:54.500 --> 09:56.333
- Good to see you again, man.
How you been?

09:56.333 --> 09:58.033
- Oh, my gosh,
what are the chances?

09:58.033 --> 09:59.467
We haven't seen each other
in four years.

