for espresso martini

32:33.233 --> 32:36.200
after about 5:00
in the afternoon,

32:36.200 --> 32:37.467
I'm gonna use decaf.

32:37.467 --> 32:39.100
- Thank you, Hannah.

32:39.100 --> 32:40.533
- Okay, Bobby.

32:40.533 --> 32:42.000
See you in the morning, bud.
- Right, brother.

32:42.000 --> 32:43.600
- Is this gluten-free?

32:43.600 --> 32:46.133
[upbeat music]

32:46.133 --> 32:47.367
- Thank you.

32:51.500 --> 32:52.734
- Grace, the apples.
Don't stop--

32:52.734 --> 32:54.667
- Oh, Jesus Christ.

32:54.667 --> 32:56.367
- Would you ladies
like another drink?

32:56.367 --> 32:57.667
- Yes!

32:57.667 --> 32:59.133
- If this drink don't
knock them out,

32:59.133 --> 33:00.633
I do not know what will.

33:00.633 --> 33:02.367
Mama needs some sleep.

33:02.367 --> 33:03.667
- 7:00 a.m. wakeup?
- Yeah.

33:03.667 --> 33:07.000
- 7:30, top deck.
- 7:30, level three.

33:07.000 --> 33:10.200
- What should we do?
Should we go to bed?

33:10.200 --> 33:12.200
- Oh, I'm so tired.

33:12.200 --> 33:13.500
- I'm actually hungry
for a snack.

33:13.500 --> 33:15.500
- On holiday,
I'm gonna eat it up.

33:15.500 --> 33:16.767
- How you doing?

33:16.767 --> 33:18.633
- We might have to do
some nachos.

33:18.633 --> 33:21.033
- Nachos?
A vegetarian nacho?

33:21.033 --> 33:22.000
- No.
- No?

33:22.000 --> 33:24.367
- All meat nachos.

33:24.367 --> 33:26.300
[tense music]

33:26.300 --> 33:28.033
- When you're out
with women like that,

33:28.033 --> 33:31.633
they order a garden salad
with a side of dressing,

33:31.633 --> 33:33.567
and then at 3:00 a.m.,
they're the first bitches

33:33.567 --> 33:35.433
at the f---ing kebab stand,
I tell you.

33:35.433 --> 33:37.233
Nachos coming up.

33:37.233 --> 33:40.233
- Thanks.
- [sighs]

33:40.233 --> 33:41.567
In my experience in yachting,

33:41.567 --> 33:44.667
going to wake up chefs
is never fun.

33:44.667 --> 33:46.433
♪ ♪

33:46.433 --> 33:47.467
[knocking]

33:48.433 --> 33:49.700
- Where's the bow line?

33:49.700 --> 33:51.133
Supposed to be in your hand.

33:51.133 --> 33:52.667
Come get me.
- F---.

33:57.600 --> 33:59.667
[dramatic music]

34:05.700 --> 34:07.166
- Like, starving.

34:07.166 --> 34:08.734
- Those are edible flowers,
right?

34:08.734 --> 34:12.567
♪ ♪

34:12.567 --> 34:15.066
- Hi, sorry.

34:15.066 --> 34:17.600
- What do you think?
Like, cheese, jalapeno...

34:17.600 --> 34:20.000
- Cheese, eat, jalapeno.
- Meat?

34:20.000 --> 34:21.166
- Yeah.
- Really?

34:21.166 --> 34:22.467
- Yeah.

34:22.467 --> 34:24.333
- What happened
to the preference sheet?

34:24.333 --> 34:25.600
Are you kidding me?

34:25.600 --> 34:27.700
[upbeat music]

34:27.700 --> 34:30.600
Done, it's perfect,
just the way it is.

34:30.600 --> 34:32.166
- Oh, shut up, stuff it.
- Couldn't change--

34:32.166 --> 34:34.333
couldn't change a thing.

34:34.333 --> 34:36.000
- Oh, you're talking
about the nachos.

34:36.000 --> 34:38.266
♪ ♪

34:38.266 --> 34:40.266
Are we ready
for some nachos?

34:40.266 --> 34:41.333
- We are.
- Okay.

34:41.333 --> 34:43.300
Enjoy.
Good sleep.

34:45.166 --> 34:47.500
- How do we go from, like,
Veganville to...

34:47.500 --> 34:49.367
f---ing nachos?

34:49.367 --> 34:53.033
- I am a vegan,
but my alter ego is not.

34:53.033 --> 34:55.233
- My alter ego is
a 16-year-old stoner.

34:58.166 --> 35:01.166
[upbeat rock music]

35:01.166 --> 35:03.300
♪ ♪

35:03.300 --> 35:04.633
[grinder whirring]

35:04.633 --> 35:06.700
♪ ♪

35:06.700 --> 35:09.100
- Good morning.
- Hi, Captain.

35:09.100 --> 35:11.500
- I want to know how
your evening was.

35:11.500 --> 35:13.734
- Your crew is so nice.

35:13.734 --> 35:15.500
- Oh, oh, thank God.
- Yeah.

35:15.500 --> 35:17.500
- We're going to an anchorage
about 18 miles away.

35:17.500 --> 35:19.367
We'll anchor.
Watersports.

35:19.367 --> 35:21.567
If you need anything,
you know where I am.

35:21.567 --> 35:23.133
- I love it.
- I appreciate that.

35:23.133 --> 35:24.133
Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

35:24.133 --> 35:25.767
[electronic music]

35:25.767 --> 35:28.000
- Deck team,
in position please.

35:28.000 --> 35:29.233
- Where do you want me, Wes?
Bow?

35:29.233 --> 35:30.500
- Yeah, bow.
Max, come back here.

35:30.500 --> 35:32.233
- Hi, guys.
- I was just texting you.

35:36.600 --> 35:39.266
- We can work our way up
from the stern to the bow.

35:39.266 --> 35:41.500
♪ ♪

35:41.500 --> 35:42.533
- Sh--.
- Stern line to oar.

35:42.533 --> 35:44.266
- Bow clear.

35:44.266 --> 35:45.767
- Oar line's off.
Clear to move.

35:45.767 --> 35:49.000
- Thank you.

35:49.000 --> 35:50.367
- Ooh!
Are we moving?

35:50.367 --> 35:52.600
- Keep communicating
distances, location.

35:52.600 --> 35:55.333
- Probably about 100 feet
to the vessel.

35:55.333 --> 35:58.200
We are now all clear
of the marina wall.

35:58.200 --> 36:00.100
- Good job, guys.

36:00.100 --> 36:03.100
[bright electronic music]

36:03.100 --> 36:10.133
♪ ♪

36:12.300 --> 36:13.500
- Time to feast.

36:13.500 --> 36:16.433
♪ ♪

36:16.433 --> 36:17.567
- Yay.

36:19.133 --> 36:20.266
- Yeah.

36:22.266 --> 36:24.233
- Perfect, perfect.
Bring it now.

36:24.233 --> 36:27.500
Monica just asked if
she could get a veggie omelet.

36:27.500 --> 36:28.633
- Write it down.
- That's fine,

36:28.633 --> 36:29.700
but can we do this--

36:29.700 --> 36:31.133
- I don't care what you do.

36:31.133 --> 36:32.133
Just get me little
sticky pads...

36:32.133 --> 36:33.400
- This is the yachting industry,

36:33.400 --> 36:35.233
not a burger joint, honey.

36:35.233 --> 36:37.400
I'm not going out with a pen
and paper to take orders.

36:37.400 --> 36:38.767
- See how this is beautiful,

36:38.767 --> 36:40.433
'cause then we have
accountability...

36:40.433 --> 36:42.033
- Yeah, that's fine.
- On both of our ends.

36:42.033 --> 36:43.100
I don't want to be rude to Bugs,
but truthfully,

36:43.100 --> 36:44.266
I've got a chief stew.

36:44.266 --> 36:45.433
I don't need two.

36:45.433 --> 36:48.533
- They're pretty much the same.

36:48.533 --> 36:50.400
- Hey, crew, please get on
your watersports gear.

36:50.400 --> 36:51.700
I'm on the bow, Captain.

36:51.700 --> 36:54.000
- Drop the anchor.

36:54.000 --> 36:57.000
♪ ♪

36:57.000 --> 36:59.433
- All right, Captain, that's
three shots at the water line.

36:59.433 --> 37:01.333
- Go ahead,
get the toys in the water.

37:01.333 --> 37:02.333
- Copy that.

37:02.333 --> 37:04.433
♪ ♪

37:04.433 --> 37:06.200
- She's gonna be on the beach
with you setting it up.

37:06.200 --> 37:07.600
- Okay, perfect.

37:07.600 --> 37:09.667
We're gonna do
a signature cocktail.

37:09.667 --> 37:13.467
- Give us a cool Hawaiian,
like, cocktail name.

37:13.467 --> 37:15.266
- [laughs]
I don't know.

37:15.266 --> 37:17.200
- You can think about it.
- Yeah.

37:17.200 --> 37:19.467
- I'm kind of thinking maybe
I should just go for a nap,

37:19.467 --> 37:22.133
and I can give Sandy
the chief stew position.

37:22.133 --> 37:24.166
- You know how to drive
a tender, right?

37:24.166 --> 37:25.667
- Mm-hmm.
- I think two people

37:25.667 --> 37:27.600
can do the picnic.

37:27.600 --> 37:30.367
And Wes and Bobby
stay onboard.

37:30.367 --> 37:32.233
- Hey, Bobby, do you mind just
holding this line here?

37:32.233 --> 37:34.467
- Just hand me the line.
We're gonna walk it around.

37:34.467 --> 37:36.333
This is how we're
gonna be more efficient.

37:36.333 --> 37:38.633
I got this.
You guys do the WaveRunners.

37:38.633 --> 37:40.500
- Captain Sandy's
got an eye on us.

37:40.500 --> 37:42.233
- Oh, that's the banana?

37:42.233 --> 37:43.633
I'll fill that up.
- Should we leave that out here?

37:43.633 --> 37:45.734
- But that could be a good thing
because, you know,

37:45.734 --> 37:47.433
we're gonna learn her way

37:47.433 --> 37:48.767
and so she doesn't get
mad at us, you know?

37:48.767 --> 37:51.233
Happy boss, happy life?

37:51.233 --> 37:52.767
[laughs]

37:52.767 --> 37:55.200
- You want to start on the side?

37:55.200 --> 37:56.433
- That's a beautiful thing.

37:56.433 --> 37:58.233
That was, like,
the easiest launch ever.

37:58.233 --> 38:00.033
- You guys like the view?
- Yeah.

38:00.033 --> 38:04.166
♪ ♪

38:04.166 --> 38:06.200
- Guys, Heather's coming in
for another run.

38:06.200 --> 38:07.767
- Does anybody want
to ride the banana?

38:07.767 --> 38:09.600
No, no pressure.

38:09.600 --> 38:11.367
♪ ♪

38:11.367 --> 38:12.533
- Cutlery's in here, okay?

38:12.533 --> 38:14.233
- Sweet, thank you.

38:14.233 --> 38:16.400
- It's out of gear, right?
- Yeah, in idle.

38:16.400 --> 38:17.500
- I don't think so.

38:17.500 --> 38:19.000
[smash]
- Sh--.

38:19.000 --> 38:20.400
- We're just gonna
tie it off here.

38:20.400 --> 38:22.100
Please shut it down.

38:22.100 --> 38:23.667
This is the most green crew
I've ever had.

38:23.667 --> 38:25.500
Let Hannah know you're here.

38:25.500 --> 38:26.533
- Okay.

38:26.533 --> 38:29.533
[upbeat dance music]

38:29.533 --> 38:30.767
♪ ♪

38:30.767 --> 38:32.533
- Whoa!
- [laughs]

38:32.533 --> 38:34.467
- Max needs help.
- I'll get the girls.

38:34.467 --> 38:36.467
We'll get everything in,
and then we'll just go in one.

38:36.467 --> 38:37.600
- Perfect.
- We don't need to be like...

38:37.600 --> 38:39.200
- All right.

38:39.200 --> 38:40.600
- Lauren, Lauren, Hannah.
Get ready.

38:40.600 --> 38:42.233
We're gonna go to the beach.
Now, now.

38:42.233 --> 38:43.667
- What's taking so long?
- All right, ladies.

38:43.667 --> 38:45.333
Are we ready?
- Thank you.

38:45.333 --> 38:47.600
- Max?
At the beach?

38:47.600 --> 38:49.367
- You're gonna love your picnic.

38:50.734 --> 38:53.700
- Definitely got a interesting
way of managing.

38:53.700 --> 38:55.633
- Oh, my gosh.

38:55.633 --> 38:57.433
- Yay.

38:57.433 --> 38:59.300
- You all right?
- Hey, Max.

38:59.300 --> 39:02.533
- Everyone's having fun, and
I'm sweating my bollocks off.

39:02.533 --> 39:04.533
- Such a glamorous life,
isn't it?

39:04.533 --> 39:05.700
- Yeah.

39:05.700 --> 39:07.567
Number one
beach picnic organizer.

39:07.567 --> 39:09.033
- It's okay.
- [groans]

39:09.033 --> 39:10.266
- Thank you.

39:11.633 --> 39:12.633
- Where's the bow line?

39:12.633 --> 39:14.033
Supposed to be in your hand.

39:14.033 --> 39:15.300
Go back to the steering wheel.

39:15.300 --> 39:16.567
You're in forward.

39:16.567 --> 39:18.400
I want you to go back out there,

39:18.400 --> 39:20.533
and I want you to practice going
in and out of reverse, okay?

39:20.533 --> 39:22.266
We're limited with crew members.

39:22.266 --> 39:24.567
I want her to feel confident
in handling that tender.

39:24.567 --> 39:26.667
I want the bow line
in your hand.

39:26.667 --> 39:29.433
Practice.
Go forward, go reverse.

39:29.433 --> 39:31.133
- But, like, we're on charter.

39:31.133 --> 39:32.667
That's not the time
to be training people.

39:32.667 --> 39:35.467
- How is the food getting here?
- Uh, tender.

39:35.467 --> 39:38.133
- That's how you learn.
Reverse.

39:38.133 --> 39:41.600
- We're right in the middle of
getting the beach picnic set up.

39:41.600 --> 39:44.333
Interior's counting on me.
I'm feeling very nervous.

39:44.333 --> 39:47.066
- Come get me--I've got to show
you how to do it.

39:47.066 --> 39:48.300
- F---.

39:48.300 --> 39:49.300
[tense music]

39:53.266 --> 39:53.500
- All right, so,

39:53.500 --> 39:54.100
- All right, so,
here's what we're gonna do.

39:55.734 --> 39:57.200
Ready?
- Oh, my God, poor Malia.

39:57.200 --> 39:58.667
- See how this bow line's here?
- Yeah.

39:58.667 --> 40:00.433
- I like that
the captain's so involved.

40:00.433 --> 40:03.033
- You worked on a dive boat,
so you understand

40:03.033 --> 40:06.133
how efficient one needs to be
on their own.

40:06.133 --> 40:09.567
- I don't know how
she hasn't snapped.

40:09.567 --> 40:11.734
- Adam, Hannah.
What's your ETA?

40:11.734 --> 40:13.133
- I'm ready when you are.
Waiting.

40:13.133 --> 40:14.433
It's all cold food.

40:14.433 --> 40:16.233
- Legend.
Thank you.

40:16.233 --> 40:18.300
- Don't stand there
and watch me.

40:18.300 --> 40:20.100
Go find something else to do.

40:20.100 --> 40:21.300
- Okay.

40:21.300 --> 40:22.734
If I was chief stew,

40:22.734 --> 40:24.333
Adam would never talk to me
that way.

40:24.333 --> 40:26.100
- And that's how
you speak your mind.

40:26.100 --> 40:27.600
- Sandy, Sandy, Hannah?

40:27.600 --> 40:30.200
If we could get a tender run
quickly with the food,

40:30.200 --> 40:31.500
that would be great.

40:31.500 --> 40:33.633
It's not the time to be
giving lessons.

40:33.633 --> 40:35.500
Can we not wait till
the guests get off

40:35.500 --> 40:37.433
and we're not in the middle
of a beach picnic?

40:37.433 --> 40:39.467
- Yes, ready to go
to the beach, guys?

40:39.467 --> 40:41.200
- Yeah.
- Awesome.

40:41.200 --> 40:42.467
All the guests are ready,
so they're just

40:42.467 --> 40:44.500
gonna bring it all together.

40:44.500 --> 40:46.166
- She's gonna send the food now,

40:46.166 --> 40:47.767
at the same time
as the guests,

40:47.767 --> 40:49.767
which is exactly what
I didn't want to do,

40:49.767 --> 40:52.033
'cause I wanted everything
set up before they got here.

40:52.033 --> 40:53.700
I really don't know
whether I'm gonna last

40:53.700 --> 40:55.433
the charter season
with this captain.

40:55.433 --> 40:57.633
Like, I'm getting annoyed,
which is really scary,

40:57.633 --> 41:00.333
'cause it's day three.
- Yeah.

41:00.333 --> 41:03.133
- This season on
"Below Deck Mediterranean"...

41:03.133 --> 41:05.100
[all toasting]

41:05.100 --> 41:08.100
- I absolutely love Croatia.
It's just so magical.

41:08.100 --> 41:09.367
- This is why you let
the captain decide

41:09.367 --> 41:10.400
where you're going.

41:10.400 --> 41:12.000
- [screaming]

41:12.000 --> 41:13.000
- It's my first time
in Croatia,

41:13.000 --> 41:14.400
and it's awesome.

41:14.400 --> 41:16.000
[laughs]

41:16.000 --> 41:18.066
- We all live, drink, eat,

41:18.066 --> 41:19.133
work together...

41:19.133 --> 41:20.500
all: Oh!

41:20.500 --> 41:22.533
I'm a yachtie.
It's what we do.

41:22.533 --> 41:24.200
- They're not wearing
any clothes.

41:24.200 --> 41:25.533
- There are unmentionable parts

41:25.533 --> 41:27.633
staring right into my eyeballs.

41:27.633 --> 41:29.000
- [laughs]
- Oh, no.

41:29.000 --> 41:30.467
- You've got beautiful women.

41:30.467 --> 41:32.066
You've got lots of money.

41:32.066 --> 41:33.367
I feel like there
is some flirting.

41:33.367 --> 41:36.100
I get distracted by the ladies.

41:36.100 --> 41:37.533
- Well,
it's got onions all in it.

41:37.533 --> 41:40.000
- Can we get another one
with no chives?

41:40.000 --> 41:41.567
- Well, that's not gonna
happen, so they can f--- off.

41:41.567 --> 41:43.533
- Sometimes the actions of one

41:43.533 --> 41:45.300
have consequences for the many.

41:45.300 --> 41:47.433
- We need somebody to help us
with a flight to Spain.

41:47.433 --> 41:49.133
- So you're their travel agent?

41:49.133 --> 41:51.166
- The sink is overflowing.
I need help.

41:51.166 --> 41:53.033
Everyone saw.

41:53.033 --> 41:54.633
- You have two co-workers

41:54.633 --> 41:56.166
with your tongue
in their mouths.

41:56.166 --> 41:57.367
- That's probably a bad idea.

41:57.367 --> 41:59.000
- Is this like a threesome?

41:59.000 --> 42:00.133
- I've never hooked up
with a crewmate.

42:00.133 --> 42:01.700
It'll make all of us look bad.

42:01.700 --> 42:04.367
- If I want to go around
and f--- everyone on this boat,

42:04.367 --> 42:05.667
that's my prerogative.

42:05.667 --> 42:07.100
- I kissed a f---ing whore.

42:07.100 --> 42:08.133
- Thanks for your support,
Lauren.

42:08.133 --> 42:09.700
Why don't you go f--- Ben?

42:09.700 --> 42:12.500
- I'm being ostracized over
this whole Bobby thing.

42:12.500 --> 42:14.667
It never ends well for the girl
that breaks girl code.

42:14.667 --> 42:16.100
- Stop, stop!
F---.

42:16.100 --> 42:17.266
I ruined it.
- Jesus Christ!

42:17.266 --> 42:18.567
- That can never happen.

42:18.567 --> 42:19.767
- I just give the guests
what they ask for

42:19.767 --> 42:21.400
on their preference sheet.

42:21.400 --> 42:23.200
- What's that,
a resting bitch face?

42:23.200 --> 42:25.734
- F--- you, bro.
- No, no, no, no!

42:25.734 --> 42:27.200
- Oh, God!
Woman down.

42:27.200 --> 42:28.433
- Don't be a smartass.

42:28.433 --> 42:30.266
- Don't tell me
what to do, Bobby.

42:30.266 --> 42:32.300
- I feel this season,
you've been a lousy chief stew.

42:32.300 --> 42:34.533
- Guys, you're now looking
at the new lead deckhand.

42:34.533 --> 42:35.734
- You guys have had relations.

42:35.734 --> 42:37.333
It's a conflict of interest.

42:37.333 --> 42:39.166
That is Leadership 101.

42:39.166 --> 42:41.033
- You cannot cross that line.

42:41.033 --> 42:42.600
- Do you want to go speak
to Captain Sandy about it?

42:42.600 --> 42:44.000
- Bobby, get over it, bro.

42:44.000 --> 42:45.533
[glass shattering]
- Holy sh--!

42:45.533 --> 42:46.600
